doc.ContractDescription: THE PROPOSED STUDY DESCRIBED BELOW HAS TWO GOALS RELATED TO THE PERFORMANCE OF THE D-SERIES BOUNDARY-LAYER-INGESTING AIRCRAFT. THE FIRST GOAL, INCORPORATED IN TASK 1 OF THIS PROPOSAL, IS TO ESTABLISH THE TRADE-OFFS BETWEEN CRUISE SPEED AND PERFORMANCE (FUEL, EMISSIONS, NOISE) AT THE CONCEPTUAL LEVEL. SPECIFICALLY, THE FOLLOWING WILL BE ESTABLISHED: (I) PERFORMANCE BENEFITS OF N+3 LEVEL TECHNOLOGY ASSUMPTIONS ON AIRCRAFT PERFORMANCE (II) PERFORMANCE BENEFITS OF THE D-SERIES CONFIGURATION COMPARED TO A BASELINE CONVENTIONAL TUBE-AND-WING AIRCRAFT (III) TRADE-OFFS BETWEEN CRUISE SPEED AND PERFORMANCE FOR BOTH CONVENTIONAL AND DSERIES CONFIGURATIONS. THE SECOND GOAL, INCORPORATED AS TASK 2, IS TO DESIGN A TRANSONIC GEOMETRY, INCLUDING AERODYNAMIC OUTER-MOLD-LINES AND ENGINE CHARACTERISTICS, OF A D8-TYPE AIRCRAFT AT A LEVEL SUITABLE FOR EXPERIMENTAL AND CFD TRANSONIC STUDIES. THIS WILL BE DONE BOTH FOR A D8 AIRCRAFT FLYING AT MACH 0.72 CRUISE SPEED, AND FOR A D8 VERSION FLYING AT A CRUISE SPEED OF MACH 0.8.
